LISBON, Sept 26 (Reuters) - Following are some of the main stories in Portuguese newspapers on Friday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

* Yes or No? Prime minister to speak of alleged improper payments in parliament after prosecutors shelve case due to  expired statue of limitations (Publico) * Novo Banco provisions 1.25 bln euros to repay hidden debt of Banco Espirito Santo placed with retail clients (Negocios) * Novo Banco to propose to long-term senior bond holders conversion into deposits (Diario Economico) * Tourism companies ending 2014 with new record numbers (Diario Economico)